TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bayar, Onur
AU  - Chemmanur, Thomas J.
AU  - Liu, Mark H.
T1  - A Theory of Capital Structure, Price Impact, and Long-Run Stock Returns under Heterogeneous Beliefs
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfv004
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 4
IS  - 2
SP  - 258
EP  - 320
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - We study an environment with short-sale constraints and heterogeneous beliefs among outsiders and between insiders and outsiders. Firm insiders choose between equity, debt, and convertible debt to raise external financing. We analyze two settings: one in which heterogeneous beliefs is the only market imperfection and another in which there are significant security issue and financial distress costs. Our model generates a pecking order of external financing different from asymmetric information models, and new predictions for capital structure, sequential tranching of securities, the price impact of security issues, and long-run stock returns. We also provide a new rationale for convertible debt issuance.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfv004
ER  - 



