TY  - JOUR
AU  - Almazan, Andres
AU  - Martín-Oliver, Alfredo
AU  - Saurina, Jesús
T1  - Securitization and Banks’ Capital Structure
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfv002
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 4
IS  - 2
SP  - 206
EP  - 238
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - Asset securitization offers banks the possibility of altering their capital structures and the financial intermediation process. This study shows that the introduction of securitization is associated with fundamental changes in the funding policies of banks. We present evidence of more intense use of securitization by banks with stronger growth opportunities, liquidity constraints, costlier alternative sources of funding, and restricted access to capital markets due to adverse selection. Securitization is observed to be higher in the pecking order of financing choices of small- and medium-sized banks and nonlisted banks, which are likely to face more severe adverse selection problems.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfv002
ER  - 



